Every athlete has his/her own goal, and BH integrates the  characteristics of different needs to design different training programs  with suitable speed and incline setting.</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p><img title="g6421c-12072301_586_586" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6421c-12072301_586_586.jpg" alt="g6421c-12072301_586_586" width="586" height="419"></p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p><img title="g6421c-12072303_586_586" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6421c-12072303_586_586.jpg" alt="g6421c-12072303_586_586" width="586" height="182"></p>\n<p>According to the data based on the training of BH Triathlon Team, BH  R&amp;D department re-designed the shock absorbing system for G6415C  treadmill. Larger contact surface not only transfers the pressure on  knees and ankles effectively, but also protects the running board while  running.</p>\n<p><img title="g6421c-12072304_586_586" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6421c-12072304_586_586.jpg" alt="g6421c-12072304_586_586" width="586" height="368"></p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p><span style="widows: 2; text-transform: none; background-color: #e7e7e7; text-indent: 0px; display: inline !important; font: bold 18px/23px arial, Arial; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; float: none; letter-spacing: normal; color: #036ea9; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; margin-top: 20px;">SDS (Soft Drop System)</span></p>\n<p style="margin-top: 30px;">A safety system designed to keep the running board to descend at a slow speed and prevents back injuries.</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><img title="g6421c-12072307_285_285" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6421c-12072307_285_285.jpg" alt="g6421c-12072307_285_285" width="285" height="156"></p>\n<p style="padding-bottom: 25px; font-size: 18px;"><strong>Contact pulse measurement system</strong></p>\n<p style="margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 200px;">The convenient design of contact pulse measurement system allows users easily and comfortably control the exercise progress.</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p><img title="g6421c-12072305_285_285" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6421c-12072305_285_285.jpg" alt="g6421c-12072305_285_285" width="285" height="156"></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 20px; padding-top: 50px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 18px;"><strong>Blue backlit Grid LCD design</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 20px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 200px;">The data readout of G6421C treadmill adopts the grid design. All the  data display locates in separate grid with big numbers and users can  read this data clearly at any circumstances.</p>\n<p style="padding-left: 20px;"><span style="font-size: 18px;"><strong>Interactive display</strong></span></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 20px; padding-bottom: 10px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 200px;"><br>The monitor ofG6421C treadmill displays not only the basic information,  including speed, incline, pulse, time, distance and calories, but also  integrated with virtual running belt which allows users to compete with  computer agent.?</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><img title="g6421c-12072308_286_286" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6421c-12072308_286_286.jpg" alt="g6421c-12072308_286_286" width="286" height="156"></p>\n<p><span style="widows: 2; text-transform: none; background-color: #e7e7e7; text-indent: 0px; display: inline !important; font: bold 18px/23px arial, Arial; white-space: normal; orphans: 2; float: none; letter-spacing: normal; color: #036ea9; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-size-adjust: auto; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;"><img title="blue-arr_11_03" src="../ipic/blue-arr_11_03.gif" alt="blue-arr_11_03" width="11" height="11">\xa0 Speed / Incline instant keys</span></p>\n<p><strong>G6421C treadmill is integrated with the convenient instant speed keys  (2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, 14, 16 km/h) and instant incline keys  (2?4?6?8?10?12?15%) which make your workout more precisely.</strong></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><img title="g6421c-12072310_286_286" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6421c-12072310_286_286.jpg" alt="g6421c-12072310_286_286" width="286" height="157"></p>\n<p>\xa0</p>\n<p style="padding-bottom: 20px; font-size: 18px;"><strong>Large control panel</strong></p>\n<p style="padding-bottom: 60px; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 200px;">According to the design of commercial use treadmills, G6421C treadmill  is integrated with large start/pause and stop buttons. It provides the durability, stops the belt  from over-stretching, and protects G6415C treadmill from static  electricity.</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><img title="g6415c-12072412_285_285" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6415c-12072412_285_285.jpg" alt="g6415c-12072412_285_285" width="285" height="156"></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 15px;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Large &amp; safe handle bar</span></strong></p>\n<p style="padding-left: 15px;">The anti-slip rubber and best angle design of handle bar could ensure the safety while workout.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><img title="g6415c-12072413_286_286" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6415c-12072413_286_286.jpg" alt="g6415c-12072413_286_286" width="286" height="156"></p>\n<p><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">Large non-slip footrests</span></strong></p>\n<p>The large non-slip rubber footrests which are in accordance with the  standards of EN957 can prevent injuries and protect the running belt.</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>\xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0 \xa0\xa0<img title="g6415c-12072414_285_285" src="../../../asset/uploads/g6415c-12072414_285_285.jpg" alt="g6415c-12072414_285_285" width="285" height="156"></p>\n<p style="margin-left: 20px;"><strong><span style="text-decoration: underline;">BH Green Power Motor</span></strong></p>\n<p style="margin-left: 20px;">The peak horse power of G6415C treadmill reaches 4.0. A wrist roller is basically a piece of wood or pipe with rope hanging from it. The rope is attached to a weight. Simple enough.</p>\n<p>How do you use it? Stand erect (yes, erect) with your arms extended straight out in front of you. Hold the wrist roller with an overhand grip. Slowly rotate one wrist a time to spin the role up the rope and lift the weight.
